 <para>This chapter lists content changes for this document since the initial
  release of &productnamereg; 1.0. </para>

 <!--lastest service pack or point release topmost-->
 <sect1 id="sec.user.20">
  <title>&productname; 2.0</title>
  
  <para>The document was updated on the following dates:</para>
  <!--list of xrefs, latest date sorted upmost-->
  <itemizedlist>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     <xref linkend="sec.user.docupdate.release" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </para>
   </listitem>
   </itemizedlist>
  
  <!--start of actual changelog-->
  <sect2 id="sec.user.docupdate.release">
   <title>September 19, 2013 (&productname; 2.0) </title>
   <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
     <term>&ostack; Service Names</term>
     <listitem>
      <!--state if new or updated, if applicable, add number of bug, fate,
      or doc comment for reference-->
      <para>Replaced code names with the &ostack; services' real names,
       according to <ulink
        url="https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Conventions#General_style_conventions"
       />. For example, talk of <emphasis>&ostack; &img;</emphasis>
       instead of <emphasis>&o_img;</emphasis>.</para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
     <term>Update to &ostack; Grizzly</term>
     <listitem>
      <para>The &dash; and the command line chapter have been updated to
       the &ostack; Grizzly release on which &productname; 2.0 is based. This
       includes the following changes:</para>
      <itemizedlist>
       <listitem>
        <para>The following section has been added: <xref
          linkend="sec.user.dash.networks"/>.</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para>Some categories have been added to the &dash;'s main screen,
         others changed name. Most importantly, the download option for RC files
         can now be found in the <guimenu>Access &amp; Security</guimenu>
         category. See <xref linkend="sec.user.dash.intro"/> and <xref
          linkend="sec.user.cli.rc"/>.</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para>Image upload is now also possible via the &dash;, though with
         limited options. For details, refer to <xref
          linkend="sec.user.dash.img"/></para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para>The workflow for some tasks has changed, most notably for the
         following ones: <xref linkend="sec.user.dash.instances.launch"/>, <xref
          linkend="pro.cloud.dash.security.rules"/>, <xref
          linkend="pro.user.dash.assign.floating.ips"/>, and <xref
          linkend="pro.user.dash.vol.attach"/>.</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para>On the command line, managing security groups, security group
         rules, and IP addresses can now also be done with the
         <command>neutron</command> commands, provided by the <systemitem
          class="resource">python-quantumclient</systemitem> package. For
         details, see <xref linkend="sec.user.cli.inst.access.security"/> and
          <xref linkend="sec.user.cli.inst.access.ips"/>. However, the former
         way of executing these tasks with the <command>nova</command> python
         client is also still supported.</para>
       </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    
